reviews.review_text:
" I need you baby to make things alright" This would be the one and only run at this monstrosity. We were on the lawn for all three nights and had a grand time.The sun was out this day and it would become a perfect night. This second show may be the best of the three, although there are a couple  bumps in the road now and then, maily from good ole Jerry :). The  first set is very good with a  surprise Box of Rain into a  rollicking Stranger. Phil is really into this one. Loser is awesome, actually perfect, and Brent really shines on the B3.I think it is a 27 beat BIODTL, they are having fun. Mid set West LA is  very cool. Far  from Me is really good with a great ending. Tennessee Jed and Bucket really  push it over the  top with screeching solos by Jerry. Healy has Bob in the echo chamber at the end of Bucket, hilarious.
Set two is  very good and  features a happening Samson to get  everyone grooving and then Brent steals the set by playing a scorching Hey Pocky Way. Estimated> Eyes is the last one for  awhile. Eyes is the better on the two and played at the faster tempo. The post space is really quite good with a long majestic Wheel, with great vocals, into a  pumping Gimme Some Lovin'. Stella was a nice suprise and is quite good.It is very reflective with more of a  somber approach and the ending is remenisent of a '74 version. A  huge T Stones with Phil once  again letting his presence be known into a power house Lovelight that has the band really driving it like we all love it. Knockin' is excellent with  superb harmonies and Brent even  does a short scat before his solo,a beautiful version. To have Brent and Phil sing in both sets was a grand treat.Quality is excellent with crisp high end and clear bass. Nice work CM.

7-22-90 Good show after Box of Rain. Phil must have had too many beers or something. IMO Phil doesn't have a good voice but I love to hear him sing. He usually projects his emotion for a song very well. Grate sound quality from C Miller once again.
pretty strong 90's Hey this show picks up more steam as it goes on. Goes to show that Bret was on fire by the end of 90....
Brent was knockin' His scat during KOHD is chilling. What a beautiful soul...RIP
this show sounds and looks great a tease if you cant download it

Night 2 Tinley Park, Final Brent Run- Su90 Solid first set from start to finish. Really dig the Stranger that follows the Box show opener. Brent is all over that thing. Otherwise, nothing particularly memorable, but it's peak-form su90 dead. Really good Loser, West LA. Brent leads a rousing rendition of Far From Me. (This one's his last fucking song for you, bitch!) Then there's a playful Jed, followed by a rocker Bucket to close. Phil sounding great in the mix. Popping off all over. Same goes for Brent.

To my ears, this is the best audio recording of this show available in the archive. The echo does start to annoy, though, in set two. I didn't hear it much in the first, I start to really hear it around Eyes. The other recordings also have the echo. At any rate, excellent Estimated with a seamless transition into Eyes. Both top notch versions. What I'm sure we would give to be there on that summer day enjoying the beauty of this show. You can almost feel the Chicago breeze among the audio. Pretty out-there drums/space. All told, this second set is a monster. 4-song 40-minute third quarter features a strong Samson opener, a funky Pocky Way, and, as mentioned, top notch Est-Eyes. It's followed by 15 minutes of drums/space as interlude, then the fourth continues and is over 40 minutes of non sop jam. Wheel goes into a Phil-heavy intro to Good Lovin->Stella Blue->Throwing Stones->Lovelight. Heaven's Door is just the perfect icing on this sweet cake of a show. Listen to Brent, poor fellow was really knockin' on it, would depart us just a few days later. 

Final Far From Me and Hey Pocky Way.
Out of sync I was at these 3, had a great time. Listening back today, it seems like the rhythm section is a bit off, just not locked in like normal. Terrific sound quality.
